# DS-0002: Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user
#
# Applies to .devcontainer/Dockerfile. Acceptable for this devcontainer:
# - it's dev-only — never deployed to a runtime host
# - the appliance the repo provisions runs Debian/Ubuntu directly via cloud-init
#   + Ansible, never this image
# - VS Code Remote Containers maps the host user in, so processes don't run
#   as container-root from the developer's perspective either
# - the Microsoft Python devcontainer base image (mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/
#   python) ships as root by design for ergonomic apt-get / pip install during
#   build; switching to a non-root USER breaks the standard devcontainer flow
#
# Revisit if the image gains a production role or the base image starts shipping
# a default non-root user that the devcontainer features actually support.
DS-0002
